               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1123" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1123" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1123" type="surname" value="HAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1123" type="given" value="THOMAS ANTHONY"></interp>THOMAS ANTHONY HAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a bootmaker, of Woolwich—on 31st March, about five o'clock in the afternoon, I was called, and saw the prisoner in the shop—he said he wanted a pair of Cossack boots—I fitted him with a pair—he said "I will have these; I have given the boy half-a-sovereign, the price is 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>."—he had not asked the price—the boy looked up astonished, and said, "You have not given me any money"—the price was 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>—he refused to take them off, and I sent for a constable—the boy was searched, and no money found on him, he bears a very good character—these boots are mine (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1124" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1124" type="surname" value="CARROLL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1124" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES CARROLL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am Mr. Hand's apprentice—on 31st March the prisoner came into the shop, and at that instant I called my master—the prisoner never said a word before he came—the first pair of boots fitted him—he said "I gave the boy half-a-sovereign"—I said, "You did not give me any money, sir"—the prisoner said, "The boy says the price of them is 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>."—I had not said so; the price was 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he had given me no money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1125" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1125" type="surname" value="FORSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1125" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FORSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a sergeant in the Royal Artillery—the prisoner belongs to that company—he was under stoppages, and has only received fourteenpence since June last—he was not likely to have half-a-sovereign.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1126" type="witnessName">
